**Concise summary:**  
The Stargate Project was a secret U.S. government program from the 1970s to the 1990s that investigated psychic phenomena, mainly remote viewing, for intelligence purposes. Despite claims of success, the project was ultimately declassified and shut down after a CIA review found no consistent evidence of effectiveness. It remains a subject of debate among believers and skeptics and has left a lasting impact on popular culture and discussions about human consciousness.